label.value: presumptive cardiac ventricle primitive heart tube

value.value: Lateral line canal that that crosses the supratemporal region posterior to the openings of the endolymphatic ducts and connects the lateral canals of each side.

definition.value: Not clear what the taxon constraints are here. The cited reference discusses two species of dogfish.

value.value: Organism subdivision that is the side of the body possessing eyes.
Organism subdivision that is the side of the body lacking eyes.
Joint that articulates the premaxilla and maxilla. Premaxillary-maxillary joint is paired.
Pharyngeal arch cartilage located between uncinate process of epibranchial 1 and pharyngobranchial 2.

definition.value: An interarcual cartilage is present in percomorph fishes (Johnson and Patterson 1993).

value.value: Scale that possesses cteni (discrete spines).
Ctenoid scale with two or three alternating rows of cteni marginally and truncated cteni submarginally. (Roberts 1993).

Neuromast of the supraorbital sensory canal in the nasal bone. It is innervated by the buccal nerve rather than by the supraorbital nerve, which invariably innervates neuromasts of the supraorbital canal. (Johnson and Patterson 1993).
Pectoral fin distal radial 1 element that is composed of bone tissue.
Pectoral fin distal radial 2 element that is composed of bone tissue.
Pectoral fin distal radial 3 element that is composed of bone tissue.
Joint that articulates the preopercle and opercle. Preopercle-opercle joint is paired.
Surface structure that is a visible mark on the body resulting from pigmentation.
Scale that is smooth-edged, round or oval and composed of acellular dermal bone lacking small spines on the posterior exposed edge. (from http://www.briancoad.com/Dictionary/introduction.htm).

definition.value: Typical of many teleosts. Some cycloid scales may have a serrated margin and are then termed spinoid scales. (from http://www.briancoad.com/Dictionary/introduction.htm).

value.value: Dermal bone that is typically associated with a fin. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

Basal fulcrum that is positioned at the dorsal or anterodorsal margin of the caudal fin. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

Basal fulcrum that is positioned at the anteroventral margin of the caudal fin. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.
Dermal bone that is an unpaired, scale-like structure. Arratia, G. 2009. Identifying patterns of diversity of the actinopterygian fulcra. Acta Zoologica (Stockholm) 90 (Suppl. 1): 220-235.

definition.value: temporarily relabeled 'fish scute' to distinguish from reptilian scute class. To DO: reconcile definitions for the two sets of classes.

value.value: The mesencephalic veins (MsV) enter the mid cerebral veins (MCeV) at the dorsal midline. THe MCeVs originate at the dorsal midline, proceede lateraly in a ventral direction to drain into the paired primordial midbrain channels (PHBC). ogai et al. 2001., Kimmel et al. 1993.
A vascular loop attached to the efferent part of the mandibular arch that forms at 3.5 dpf. Isogai et al. 2001.
The branch of the afferent branchial artery that continues posteriodorsally. Isogai et al. 2001.
The anterioventral proceeding branch of the afferent branchial artery. Isogai et al. 2001.
